            <h2>Safety Measures</h2>
            <p>
                PolyTransport prioritizes the safety and well-being of its users. A range of safety measures has been implemented to create a secure environment for all stakeholders involved in the college bus system.
            </p>
            <h3>Key Safety Measures Include:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Real-time Monitoring:</strong> The buses are equipped with advanced GPS systems for real-time monitoring. This allows continuous tracking of bus locations, ensuring accurate arrival and departure information.</li>
                <li><strong>Emergency Response Plan:</strong> PolyTransport has a comprehensive emergency response plan in place. In the event of unforeseen circumstances, the system is designed to respond promptly, ensuring the safety of passengers and staff.</li>
                <li><strong>Regular Maintenance Checks:</strong> Each bus undergoes regular maintenance checks to ensure optimal performance and minimize the risk of breakdowns. Trained technicians conduct thorough inspections to address any potential safety concerns.</li>
                <li><strong>Driver Training Programs:</strong> Bus drivers undergo rigorous training programs, covering defensive driving, passenger safety, and emergency procedures. This ensures that drivers are well-prepared to handle various situations responsibly.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                These safety measures collectively contribute to a secure and reliable college bus system within PolyTransport.
            </p>
        </section>

